(40, 1, 8, 11, 15, 24, 24, 'Josaphat begat Joram', 'Connection of Asa and Jehoshaphat', 'Both passages emphasize the lineage from Asa to Jehoshaphat, highlighting the continuation of the Davidic line. Matthew 1:8 lists Josaphat as Asa''s son, while 1 Kings 15:24 confirms Jehoshaphat''s reign following Asa.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 1, 8, 11, 22, 2, 50, NULL, 'Connection of Kings and Lineage', 'This connection highlights the lineage of Jehoshaphat, who is mentioned in both passages. Matthew 1:8 establishes Asa as his ancestor, while 1 Kings 22 details Jehoshaphat''s reign and actions as king of Judah.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 1, 8, 12, 3, 1, 1, 'Josaphat begat Joram', 'Connection of Kings and Reigns', 'This connection highlights the lineage of kings, as both passages mention the reign of Jehoshaphat and his descendants. The mention of Jehoram in 2 Kings directly follows the genealogy in Matthew, linking the two narratives of royal succession.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
